<title>BOLIVIA: SOCCER SHOWCASE-BRAZIL V PARAGUAY STATISTICS.</title>
<headline>SOCCER SHOWCASE-BRAZIL V PARAGUAY STATISTICS.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CRUZ, Bolivia 1997-06-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Statistics for Sunday's Copa America quarter-final between Brazil and Paraguay:</p>
<p>Brazil</p>
<p>World champions -- 1958, 1962, 1970, 1994</p>
<p>South American champions -- 1919, 1922, 1949, 1989</p>
<p>Biggest win -- 10-1 v Bolivia (April 4, 1949), 9-0 v Colombia (March 24, 1957)</p>
<p>Biggest defeat -- 6-0 v Uruguay (September 18, 1920)</p>
<p>Most goals scored in game -- 10-1 win v Bolivia (April 4, 1949)</p>
<p>Most goals conceded in game -- 8-4 defeat v Yugoslavia, June 3, 1934)</p>
<p>Paraguay</p>
<p>Best World Cup performance --1986, second round</p>
<p>South American champions -- 1953, 1979</p>
<p>Biggest win -- 7-0 v Bolivia (April 30, 1949),</p>
<p>Biggest defeat -- 8-0 v Argentina (October 20, 1926)</p>
<p>Most goals scored in a game -- 7-0 win v Bolivia (April 30, 1949)</p>
<p>Most goals conceded in a game --  8-0 defeat v Argentina (October 20, 1926) and 8-1 defeat v Argentina (December 8, 1964)</p>
<p>Brazil v Paraguay</p>
<p>Games played: 64</p>
<p>Brazil wins: 41</p>
<p>Draws: 16</p>
<p>Paraguay wins: 7</p>
</text>
